            "answer_text": "A list, based on what can be cited in research: Documentary filmsYouTube and other online videosMagazinesNewspapersWebsitesBrochuresPamphletsGenealogical recordsPatent recordsGovernment records (such as legislation, court proceedings, executive orders, speeches, and the like)Encyclopedias (online and offline)Primary source documents (diaries, receipts, the like)ArticlesScientific research studies, abstracts, papers, what have youOral historiesInterviewsPersonal experiences\u2014experiments, observation, etc.Art piecesImagesPodcastsRadio programsTV showsMicrofilm/microficheThere are many more, but these are the types of research sources commonly cited and available online and at libraries/media centres. ",
